Reasoning: The paper focuses on meta-learning algorithms for few-shot computer vision, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of meta-learning algorithms also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for few-shot learning, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper introduces a novel algorithm for few-shot object detection, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO).
